A vintage 1950s advertising illustration style scene showing a massive, impossibly complex machine with countless gears, pipes, valves, and blinking panels towering over a tiny bewildered businessman in a fedora and suit, who stands at its base scratching his head. The machine sprawls across an entire factory floor, with steam venting from random pipes and conveyor belts leading nowhere. In the background, a sleek black limousine waits with an open door, suggesting escape. Warm sepia and muted teal color palette with halftone dot texture typical of mid-century print advertisements.
